About the Series:
The series is primarily set in Yorkshire, and follows the work of two detectives that are 
thrown together as partners. Complete opposites. Different backgrounds, different beliefs, 
different styles. They get on each other's nerves.

Episode 1 "Under World"
Dalziel and Pascoe investigate when the skeleton of missing miner Billy Farr is found 
in a mineshaft in the Yorkshire coalfields,

Episode 2 "Child's Play"
The funeral of an elderly Italian woman is interrupted by the arrival of her son, 
thought missing since 1944

Episode 3 "Bones and Silence"
Dalziel is happily relaxing in flat after a hard day's work, when across the street, 
he notices a man pull a gun on his wife in the first floor flat.

Episode 4 "The Wood Beyond"
A group of animal rights protesters who break into a medical facility find more than 
they bargain for when one escapes from the clutches of security into the nearby woods, 
only to find the remains of a dead body.
